h=611 border=0><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Character Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>30 - 39</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Solo/Group</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Solo</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Zone</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>South Karana</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>XP</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>8</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Loot</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>6</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Danger</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>9</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Mob</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Vhalen Nostrolos</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Mob Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>31</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Location</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>-200,-200</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Factions</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>-LeagueofAntonicanBards</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Spells Used</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Dooming Darkness, Boil Blood, Venom of the Snake, Vampiric Curse, Spirit Tap, Invoke Fear, Intensify Death, Feign Death</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Strategy</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Vhalen is a Bard that pretty much hits like a Monk. Fast and powerful, he can deal up to 150 points of damage per round with his two attacks. He spawns just by the small pond close to loc -200,-200 every 7 minutes.<br>I will break down this strategy for players below level 34 and past level 34.<br>Levels 30 to 33:<br>Well, below level 34 you don't have Root or Invoke Fear so you will have to rely on your pet. You can hunt Vhalen without a pet, but it is safer to have one. So, find Vhalen, sit a little far away from him and cast a pet. Med to full and buff him with Intensify Death. Once you are ready, get within casting range and pull with Darkness. Immediately send your pet after him. If Darkness was resisted, recast it until it sticks. Now you have two options. First, you can try Fearing Vhalen. If Fear is successful, the battle ahead won't be a hard one. The problem is at level 30-33, you will be using a low level Fear spell that will be often resisted. You won't have time to recast Fear a few times. By the time you pull it off, your pet will be severely hurt and you will be a little low on mana. So, if you want to try it, do it once or twice maximum. If it is resisted, move to the second option. If not, simply cast Boil Blood and Spirit Tap him till dead.<br>Second option is a little safer in my opinion. After you pulled with Darkness and sent your pet to battle, cast Boil Blood and move a little close to him. He will start following you. Move back slowly but fast enough so that he doesn't catch up with you. By doing this, he will constantly try to reach you and won't return fire against your pet. Every now and then, turn around and run to a casting distance. Spirit Tap him and repeat the process. You will be close to out of mana by the time Vhalen dies.<br>Levels 34 to 39:<br>Now you have root and Invoke Fear, which makes the battles are a lot easier. And the XP is better also since you won't need a pet anymore. Once again, you could do it two ways.<br>First, you can use Root. Pull with Root and if resisted, reapply until it sticks. Once you get it off, move back to a safe casting distance and start stacking DoTs. Cast Venom of the Snake and Boil Blood, reapplying Root when needed. Vampiric Curse him when close to dead and finish him off with Spirit Tap. If you got Vampiric Curse on, cast Call of Bones to speed up your meding process.<br>The second way you can do this is by using Invoke Fear. Pull with Darkness, reapplying if resisted. As soon as it sticks, cast Invoke Fear. Since this is a level 34 spell, it will be rarely resisted. When you get it off, go ahead and cast Venom of the Snake and Boil Blood. Just go after him and cast an occasional Spirit Tap to speed up the process. Reapply Invoke Fear when needed. You can even med every now and then during the battle since Vhalen will be pretty much helpless. Cast Vampiric Curse before Vhalen goes down and finish him off with Spirit Tap. Remember, Root will cancel the Darkness effect so if you are going for this strategy, do not cast Root.<br>Well, there you go. Vhalen is pretty good for those looking for some quick XP. Loot is pretty poor though. He usually drops a few gold pieces and a maximum of 4 plat per kill. He also drops a 2g Flute, so don't even bother keeping them.<br>A few comments. You won't be fighting close to any zones, so don't try running to zone unless you got a good head start. But the real good option in case a battle goes wrong is to Feign Death. Since Vhalen is a level 30 mob, Feign Death should always work. So, if you see you are loosing the fight, simply move far away from Vhalen spawning point and Feign. He will forget about you and return to the pond. Wait a little while, get up, med, and do it again. If you are not careless, you shouldn't die here, ever. One last thing. Vhalen will hurt your faction with the League of Antonican Bards. But as Necros, why do we care?</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Author</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'><a href ='mailto:skyshade@eqnecro.com'>Skyshade Lusaris</td></tr><tr></table><br><br><table border='0' width=611><tr><td width='100%' colspan='2' bgcolor='#21456B'><p align='left' style='word-spacing: 0; margin: 0'><b><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Additional Comments</font></b></td></tr><td width='17%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Onnyx</font></td><td width='83%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Vhalen Nostrolo is the bard that stands by the well in South Karana near the Centaur Village. He is level 31, spawns every 7 minutes and can double attack for mid 70's. This spot is heavily camped so I developed a strategy to get the most out of this spawn as possible when I do get it. As you know the best XP comes from fighting without your pet. This can be very dangerous due to the damage he can deal and the fact that dooming darkness can resist and you have no time to try and recast without regaining concentration. I have finally found a way around the ever dreaded darkness resist. Spells you will need are Dooming Darkness, Boil Blood, Feign Death, Fear, and at 34 you have Venom of snake and Invoke Fear. First off when Vhalen spawns stand just outside your casting range, keep inching in until you are able to cast Dooming Darkness. If Darkness resists, immediately cast Feign Death, he will not reach you and head back towards the well. When he gets back to the well feel free to stand up and med if you wish, since he is under level 35 he will always forget you attacked him. Repeat this until Darkness sticks. When Dooming Darkness sticks, walk backwards until your spells refresh and cast Boil Blood, walk backwards again until your spells refresh and cast fear. If this is done properly you should not have a scratch on you. Once feared cast Vampiric Curse, at lower levels you might want to cast Shock of Poison a few times and re-fear if it should break. If you are level 34 or over instead of Shock of Poison cast Venom of Snake and Invoke Fear. At this point sit and med. You should soon see "You Gained Experience" If you don't have Auto-Med (level 35) you might want to keep an eye on him to make sure fear sticks. Standard loot for him is a wooden flute, up to 4pp in cash and rarely has some mid level research components (for all pure casters). At level 35 I was using this strategy and was using 2 bubbles maybe 2 and a half bubbles of mana if I had to re-fear. You should be full mana without using Allure or CoB bef! ore he respawns. Have fun with Vhalen and tell him I said hello =) btw- should I come by please let me have the spawn I am about to outgrow him and would like to give him 1 last farewell camp =)</font></td></tr><td width='17%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'><a href ='mailto:ttoomey@omm.com ?subject=Hunting Guide for Vhalen Nostrolos on EqNecro'>Taiggy</a></font></td><td width='83%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Ok, here is my solo strategy for a level 30 DE necro for this bard mob Vhalen in the South Karanas.  He is located near a fountain around pos 4 pos 15 not exactly sure on Loc but these are very close.  I keep Feign memed as it will fake him out if need be.

 

Ok here we go. buff your pet. cast allure on yourself, send pet then cast darkness on mob. Cast Vampiric curse, then heat blood on mob and then fear. If fear doesn't stick make sure to check pets hp as this guy hits pretty hard and he is fast. if pet is low heal him then try fear again. if fear sticks let pet whack him and chase him. and cast DD's and drains till he is mush. If the fears don't stick make sure to check pet and DD him to death quick

 

One thing to remember. Try to cast Allure on yourself as you might need more mana.  And if fear is not sticking heal the pet he will save your life. This mob is yellow to me at 30.

 

Now in a 2 man group at 30 we whacked him pretty quick. DD darkness etc... he is very good exp and drops up to 5pp and a flute that sells for about 3gp. I have seen lev 40's solo him for exp.

 

Safe Journeys and good hunting.</font></td></tr><td width='17%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'><a href ='mailto:kenua@hotmail.com ?subject=Hunting Guide for Vhalen Nostrolos on EqNecro'>Kenua Soulsiphoner</a></font></td><td width='83%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Since the introduction of the epic quests there is a lvl 50 mob very near Vhalen Nostrolos and if you fear him he will run straight to this beast for protection....=dead :(<br><br>

But luckily you can still beat him with ease at lvl 30+...here is how I do it.<br><br>

First make a good con pet and med to full. Then buff pet with intensify death and pull with darkness, if it is resisted fein and med again untill  it sticks. After darkness sticks start with the dots, not fear. Keep doting him untill you can hardly see the well and then fear and send in pet. I use about 2 1/2 bubs of mana at lvl 32 and take no dammage this way...but you  don't agro the lvl 50 who will turn you into a sticky paste necro paste and your pet into bone dust. 
<br><br>
Have fun with Vhalen Nostrolos, he is very easy to kill and the exp is great, about 1/5 bub per kill at lvl 32 :)</font></td></tr></table></td></table></div>